# Cursor Rules

HarnessKit is a FOSS-first TypeScript runtime layer for production AI agents.

- Keep the core engine framework-agnostic and provider-neutral.
- Do not add runtime dependencies unless they are explicitly approved or already part of the project plan.
- Preserve the `IStateStore` abstraction; database-specific logic must stay behind adapters.
- Enforce every field promised by `haas.config.yaml`; parsed config that is not enforced is a broken product contract.
- Run `npm run check` before marking implementation work complete.
